        "text": "The document is an ERCOT fee schedule effective October 1, 2024. It outlines various fees related to ERCOT services, which are non-refundable unless specified by ERCOT Protocols.\n\n1. **Private Wide Area Network (WAN) Fees**:\n   - Based on actual costs for procuring, using, maintaining, and connecting to third-party networks for ERCOT WAN communications.\n   - Initial installation or reconfiguration costs capped at $7,000.\n   - Monthly network management fee capped at $450.\n\n2. **ERCOT Load Resource Registration and Generator Interconnection or Modification Fees**:\n   - $500 for registering a new Load Resource.\n   - Additional $500 if increasing MW size by more than 20% or changing registration type.\n   - Generator registration fees:\n     - $2,300 for Settlement Only Distribution Generators (SODGs).\n     - $8,000 for generators under 10 MW.\n     - $14,000 for generators 10 MW or greater.\n   - $8,000 for changing an existing SODG to a Distribution Generation Resource (DGR).\n\nThe document provides specific fee amounts and conditions for various registration and modification scenarios.",
