        "score": 0.5075657,
        "text": "The document page is from the ERCOT Nodal Protocols and focuses on Section 26: Securitization Default Charges. It provides definitions for various variables related to energy market activities, specifically concerning securitization default charges. Here's a summary of the key terms:\n\n1. **SDCMMATOT**: Represents the total maximum MWh activity for a counter-party.\n\n2. **RTMG**: Refers to the real-time metered generation by a market participant per settlement point per resource, measured in MWh.\n\n3. **SDCRTIMG**: Indicates the securitization default charge for real-time metered generation per market participant, excluding certain resources and intervals.\n\n4. **RTDCIMP**: Describes the real-time DC import per QSE per settlement point, focusing on the DC tie schedule submitted by a market participant.\n\n5. **SDCRTDCIMP**: Covers the securitization default charge for real-time DC import per market participant.\n\n6. **RTAMLEXSECM**: Details the real-time adjusted metered load excluding load exempt from sub M, per market participant per settlement point.\n\n7. **SDCRTAML**: Defines the securitization default charge for real-time adjusted metered load per market participant.\n\n8. **RTQQES**: Refers to the QSE-to-QSE energy sale per market participant per settlement point, measured in MW.\n\n9. **SDCRTQQES**: Indicates the securitization default charge for QSE-to-QSE energy sales per market participant.\n\n10. **RTQQEP**: Describes the QSE-to-QSE energy purchase per market participant per settlement point, measured in MW.\n\nEach term is associated with specific calculations and conditions related to energy trading and securitization within the ERCOT system.",
