d in this document. What milestones do I need to keep track of? Figure 2: Major Milestones How long does it take?  ...    Estimated Duration (days) (from completion of the prior Responsible Result if process process - Some processes Party  ...    Entity documentation is provided. RARF provided to Interconnecting GINR deemed Up to 10 ERCOT Entity incomplete/rejected ERCOT Screening Study Up to 90 ERCOT Decision to proceed to Interconnecting Full Interconnection Up to 180 GINR Cancellation Entity Study (FIS) FIS assigned to a  TSP Up to 5 ERCOT ERCOT mediates Interconnecting Negotiation of FIS study Up to 60 discussions between IE and Entity and TSP scope/pricing TSP Complete RARF  ...    Checklist Commissioning, requests are rejected Figure 3-Key Process Duration and Deadlines STAGE 1: INTERCONNECTION  ...    the applicability of the interconnection process for a specific project. Stage 1 of the Generation Interconnection Process is described below in five steps:\n\n1.1.c.1. GINR and Screening Study 1.1.c.2. Full Interconnection Study (FIS)\n\n1.1.c.3. Negotiation of Interconnection Agreement 1.1.c.4. Submitting a RARF with Resource data for planning models\n\n1.1.c.5. Protocol Compliance Review  ...    In addition to submitting the GINR application forms, the Interconnecting Entity must pay an ERCOT Security Screening Study fee. The Screening Study fee will be determined by the capacity of the proposed resource. Please refer to the current ERCOT Fee Schedule posted on the ERCOT website for the ERCOT Security Screening Study fee.2 ERCOT may take up  ...    Upon completion of the Screening Study, the Interconnecting Entity has 180-days to notify ERCOT in writing of its  ...    A checklist describing the steps taken by ERCOT in the Screening Study is included in Appendix D. As a part of each  ...    performing this SSO screening study. 3 STEP 2: FULL INTERCONNECTION STUDY (FIS) The FIS is a set of 4 to 6 studies conducted by the TSP under an agreement with the Interconnecting Entity."
